# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Output of the go coverage tool, specifically when used with LiteIDE
*.out

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Go workspace file
go.work

# Environment variables
.env

# IDEs
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?

# Project specific
bin/
*.log
# Anchored to bin/ so the source directory cmd/booking-cli/ stays
# tracked. The previous unanchored `booking-cli` pattern silently
# hid every file under cmd/booking-cli/ — every PR that added a
# new file there had to use `git add -f` to override.
/bin/booking-cli
# Stray binary from `go build ./cmd/booking-cli` (no -o flag) at repo
# root. Anchored so cmd/booking-cli/ stays tracked.
/booking-cli

# Claude Code runtime artifacts (scheduled-task locks, etc.) — not
# project state; per-machine.
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# Benchmark run artifacts — generated by scripts/benchmark_compare.sh
# and scripts/benchmark_gc.sh. Each run produces ~2-40 MB of raw k6
# output + pprof profiles + GC metrics CSVs. The summary is already
# captured in PR descriptions and PROJECT_SPEC §9.
#
# Historical Feb 2026 runs (20260215_* to 20260218_*) remain tracked
# as reference baselines. New runs are ignored by default; commit a
# specific directory with `git add -f` if the results are notable
# enough to preserve.
docs/benchmarks/20260412_*/
docs/benchmarks/20260413_*/
docs/benchmarks/20261*/
docs/benchmarks/2027*/

# D8 browser demo (Vite + React + TS at demo/) — node_modules + build
# output are derived from package.json + sources; never commit them.
demo/node_modules/
demo/dist/
demo/.env
demo/.env.local
